  "user_id": 1196,
  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Single Backing Track\r\n\r\nIn this [Diary of a Song video](https://youtu.be/ZpMNJbt3QDE?t=320), Ed Sheeran describes how they created the song Shape Of You. He points out how the song has a single track that loops throughout the entire song - \r\n\r\n> This song is just one loop the whole way through... so everything else is a surprise. Every time you start getting bored of it, something new comes in or drops out.\r\n\r\nApply this idea to a song of your own using tracks from I Need a Dollar by Aloe Blacc. The workspace has been setup so a single track loops 15 times - you get to pick the track, then decide how you can layer other tracks on top of it.\r\n\r\n1) Pick your underlying track to loop the entire song [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:play_workspace)\r\n2) Use loops and rests to create small moments that appear every once in a while in the song\r\n\r\nListen to the example for what this could sound like, or look at the timeline below for one possible way to create this song\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/018f90620e474059e6ba1288615cdeed-image-1744342208400.png)\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
